About Ozempic

Ozempic (semaglutide) is used to improve blood sugar control in adults with type 2 diabetes. Ozempic is covered by most Medicare and insurance plans, but some pharmacy coupons or cash prices could help offset the cost. Ozempic is a GLP-1 Agonist which works by increasing insulin release and reducing appetite. The most common form of Ozempic is a 2mg prefilled pen. Ozempic is also available as a 3mg prefilled pen. There are currently no generic alternatives for Ozempic. Your out-of-pocket cost can be reduced to as little as $25 per 28-, 56-, or 84-day supply with a maximum savings limit of $150 per 28-day supply with an Ozempic manufacturer coupon.

Common questions about Ozempic pricing

How much is Ozempic without insurance?
expand_more

GoodRx has partnered with Novo Nordisk, the maker of Ozempic, to lower the price to $995.00 for eligible patients not using insurance. Terms and conditions apply. Additionally, Novo Nordisk currently offers a Manufacturer Coupon where commercially insured patients may pay as little as $25.00 per prescription.

Does Ozempic have a Manufacturer Coupon?
expand_more

Yes. Ozempic manufacturer Novo Nordisk currently offers a Manufacturer Coupon where commercially insured patients may pay as little as $25.00 per prescription.

Is there a generic for Ozempic?
expand_more

Currently, there is no generic for Ozempic. However, GoodRx coupons, manufacturer copay cards, and patient assistance programs can help offset your cost.

How can I save on Ozempic?
expand_more

There are a few ways to save on Ozempic. GoodRx coupons can help lower the price to $995.00 per fill. Additionally, manufacturer Novo Nordisk currently offers a Manufacturer Coupon and Novo Nordisk currently offers a Patient Assistance Program to help eligible patients save.

Does Ozempic have a Patient Assistance Program?
expand_more

Yes, Novo Nordisk currently offers a Patient Assistance Program where uninsured patients may receive their prescription at $0.00.
